      <description>&lt;p&gt;TmMgGaO&lt;sub&gt;4&lt;/sub&gt; is one of a number of recently-synthesized quantum magnets that are proposed to realize important theoretical models. Here the authors demonstrate the agreement between detailed experimental measurements and state-of-the-art predictions based on the 2D transverse field triangular lattice Ising model.&lt;/p&gt;
